ZH: 我们必须逃出这座城市才能躲避病毒。
EN: We must escape the city to avoid the virus.

ZH: 他逃走了，警方正在全力追捕。
EN: He escaped, and the police are now chasing him.

ZH: 她害怕面对现实，只想逃避问题。
EN: She is afraid to face reality and only wants to escape her problems.

ZH: 他总是逃避责任，从来不愿意承担后果。
EN: He always avoids responsibility and never wants to face the consequences.

ZH: 我们逃不过时间的洪流，最终会老去。
EN: We cannot escape the flow of time and will eventually grow old.

ZH: 她试图逃避眼前的困境，却陷入更深的泥潭。
EN: She tried to escape her current predicament but ended up in an even deeper mess.

ZH: 逃脱困境需要勇气和智慧。
EN: Escaping from difficulties requires courage and wisdom.

ZH: 他在深夜逃跑，以免被发现。
EN: He escaped in the middle of the night to avoid being caught.

ZH: 逃离城市喧嚣，去远方寻找内心的宁静。
EN: Escape from the hustle and bustle of the city to find inner peace in the distance.

ZH: 遭遇危险时，我们应该冷静思考，而不是盲目逃跑。
EN: When faced with danger, we should think calmly instead of fleeing blindly.

ZH: 无论多艰难，也不能逃避面对挑战。
EN: No matter how difficult, we must not escape from facing challenges.

ZH: 逃避现实只会让问题变得更加棘手。
EN: Escaping reality will only make problems more difficult.

ZH: 在这个关键时刻，我们不能逃避责任。
EN: At this critical moment, we cannot evade our responsibilities.

ZH: 他总是试图逃避解决问题的责任。
EN: He always tries to escape the responsibility of solving problems.

ZH: 没有人能逃脱生老病死的宿命。
EN: No one can escape the fate of aging, illness, and death.

ZH: 在困境中逃避只会让问题更加复杂。
EN: Escaping from difficulties will only make the problem more complex.

ZH: 我们应该勇敢面对困难，而不是逃避。
EN: We should face difficulties bravely instead of escaping from them.

ZH: 逃避现实只会让事情变得更糟。
EN: Escaping from reality will only make things worse.

ZH: 在逆境中逃避解决问题永远不是解决之道。
EN: Escaping from solving problems in adversity is never the solution.

ZH: 她在恐惧中逃出火灾现场。
EN: She escaped from the fire scene in fear.
